Assignment Name: Mini Project Proposal
Title: Student Placement Prediction System
Problem Statement

In today’s competitive job market, predicting whether a student will get placed during campus recruitment is a challenging task for both students and institutions. The objective of this project is to develop a Student Placement Prediction System that uses Machine Learning techniques to predict the likelihood of a student being placed based on academic and skill-related factors. This system can assist students in identifying areas of improvement and help institutions enhance training strategies.

Dataset Description

The dataset will consist of key attributes that influence placement outcomes. The selected features include:

CGPA: Represents the academic performance of the student
Internship Experience: Indicates whether the student has completed internships (Yes/No or number of internships)
Skills Score: A numerical score representing technical and soft skills
Aptitude Score: Score obtained in aptitude or logical reasoning tests

The target variable will be:

Placement Status: Whether the student is placed or not (0 = Not Placed, 1 = Placed)

The dataset can be either manually created for experimentation or collected from real-world sources such as college placement records.

Proposed Algorithms

To build the prediction model, the following Machine Learning algorithms will be used:

Logistic Regression: A simple and effective classification algorithm suitable for binary outcomes
Random Forest: An ensemble learning method that improves prediction accuracy by combining multiple decision trees

These algorithms will be trained and compared to determine which provides better performance.

Methodology
Data Collection: Gather or create a dataset with relevant features
Data Preprocessing: Handle missing values, normalize data, and encode categorical variables
Feature Selection: Identify important features affecting placement
Model Training: Train Logistic Regression and Random Forest models
Model Evaluation: Evaluate models using accuracy and other metrics
Prediction: Use the trained model to predict placement for new students
Expected Output
A prediction indicating whether a student will be Placed or Not Placed
Accuracy score of the trained model
Feature importance analysis showing which factors influence placement the most
Conclusion

This project provides a practical application of Machine Learning in the education domain. By predicting student placement outcomes, it helps students understand their strengths and weaknesses and enables institutions to improve training programs. The system demonstrates how data-driven decision-making can enhance career planning and recruitment processes.